      "source": [
        "### Creating a Daft DataFrame of Strings\n",
        "\n",
        "YouDaft provides several ways to create a DataFrame. To create a DataFrame from a list of strings, you can use `daft.from_pylist` where each dictionary in the list represents a row and its keys are column names. Alternatively, you can first create a pandas DataFrame and then convert it to a Daft DataFrame using `daft.from_pandas`."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 190
        },
        "id": "e8f4caa3",
        "outputId": "776cf542-5cd6-4e54-a798-6d16e5fb6d2a"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Example 1: Using daft.from_pylist\n",
        "data = [\n",
        "    {\"text\": \"Hello Daft\"},\n",
        "    {\"text\": \"This is a string DataFrame\"},\n",
        "    {\"text\": \"Another example\"}\n",
        "]\n",
        "df_daft_pylist = daft.from_pylist(data)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Daft DataFrame created with daft.from_pylist:\")\n",
        "df_daft_pylist.show()"
      ],
      "execution_count": 4,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {
